---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import MainLayout from '@layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Divider from '@components/Divider.astro';
import labImage from '@assets/emma-jussi-labra.jpg';
import { paths } from '@data/paths';

const title = 'About us';
const description =
  'Clouder is on a mission to unlock the hidden value in real estate portfolios. We replace silos and fragmented operations with investment-grade data and turn it into measurable asset value.';
---

<MainLayout title={title} description={description} headerClass="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900">
  <section class="bg-linear-to-b from-white to-transparent dark:from-neutral-900">
    <div class="container-narrow mb-8 py-16 text-center sm:py-20 md:py-24 lg:py-28 xl:py-32">
      <h1
        class="mb-8 text-3xl font-semibold text-neutral-950 md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl dark:text-neutral-50"
      >
        Unlocking hidden value in real estate portfolios
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">{description}</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Divider />
  <section class="container py-16 sm:py-20 md:py-24 lg:py-28 xl:py-32">
    <h2
      class="mb-6 max-w-lg text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-950 md:text-3xl dark:text-neutral-50"
    >
      Turning building data into asset intelligence
    </h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-12 gap-y-6 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-x-16 xl:gap-x-20">
      <p>
        We have been on the other side of this problem. As real estate investors, owners, and asset
        managers, we have sat through the transactions, reviewed the reports, and managed the
        portfolios. And we kept seeing the same thing: assets that should be consuming less energy
        and performing better. Every wasted euro is permanently off the asset value. So we decided
        to build what the industry was missing.
      </p>
      <p>
        We built a direct connection to building systems (not through cloud APIs, but at the source)
        that turns real building data into real operational value. Clouder doesn't just read data.
        It acts on it, in real time, and learns from the result. Every building gets smarter,
        consumes less energy, and produces fewer emissions. Every new asset benefits from what we
        have already learned across the portfolio. The system compounds.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Divider />
  <section class="container py-16 sm:py-20 md:py-24 lg:py-28 xl:py-32">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-12 gap-y-8 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-x-16 xl:gap-x-20">
      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-950 md:text-3xl dark:text-neutral-50">
          Built by people who know commercial real estate and technology
        </h2>
        <p>
          Clouder is built on an uncommon combination of expertise: decades of experience in
          large-scale commercial real estate development, transactions and institutional asset
          management, paired with deep knowledge in data architecture, real-time systems engineering
          and enterprise-scale technology infrastructure. That breadth of competence across both
          disciplines is what makes it possible to build something the industry has not seen before.
        </p>
      </div>
      <Image
        src={labImage}
        alt="People in hardware laboratory"
        class="rounded bg-neutral-500/10 text-transparent lg:mt-1.5"
        width={720}
        layout="constrained"
      />
    </div>
  </section>
  <Divider />
  <section class="container py-16 sm:py-20 md:py-24 lg:py-28 xl:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-950 md:text-3xl dark:text-neutral-50">
        The gap is measurable.<br />So is closing it.
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-8">
        Clouder works with commercial real estate funds, asset managers, and large-scale investors
        who manage portfolios where operational inefficiency has real, measurable consequences. If
        you suspect the gap between your portfolio's current value and its potential is larger than
        it should be, we should talk.
      </p>
      <div>
        <a
          href={paths.contact.href}
          class="inline-flex h-10 cursor-pointer items-center justify-center gap-1 rounded bg-neutral-800 px-4 text-center text-sm font-[550] text-nowrap text-neutral-50 transition select-none hover:bg-neutral-950 active:bg-neutral-950 dark:bg-neutral-200 dark:text-neutral-950 dark:hover:bg-white dark:active:bg-white"
        >
          Get in touch
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
